Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a theory of concurrency for ensuring liveness properties of distributed systems without making fairness assumptions. This involves the study of process algebra, temporal logic, and semantic models, which are all relevant to the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the need for new axiomatic bases for process algebras and new congruence formats for operational semantics, which are topics in the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the study of language or model extensions for accurately specifying systems without fairness assumptions, which falls under the sub-categories of Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions the treatment of time and probability, which are topics in the sub-category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
